The DIY multideck is a deck of 162 playing cards (3 standard decks) that lets you play hundreds of existing games by using a bit of imagination and sometimes drawing on the cards. The cards are waterproof and come in a transportation bag, making them **ideal for travelling**! üåç

The DIY multideck features 4 different kinds of decks: Basic, 3D, Sequential and Pyramidal. Plus, game-specific decks by drawing on the cards. Each game uses a different subset of cards that can be found in the [official website](/), or you can map your own games after learning the deck's features.

The DIY multideck has been created by [Maurici Abad](https://mauriciabad.com), a young software engineer from Spain, with a lot of thought and care. The deck was heavily inspired by [The Everdeck](https://thewrongtools.wordpress.com/2019/10/10/the-everdeck/), and it supports [almost all games for it](https://boardgamegeek.com/geeklist/230703/games-playable-everdeck), plus [many more](/games). It can be bought on the [official website](/), directly from the creator.

