## Feature list

- **Game systems**: Many arrangements of cards that let you play different games.
  - **Basic deck**: 8 suits of 15 ranks + 4 suits of 10 ranks
    - 12 suits of 10 ranks.
    - 8 suits of 15 ranks.
    - Remaining cards can be used to either add more ranks to some suits or add new suits of fewer ranks.
  - **3D deck** of 5x3x10: 5 colors √ó 3 shapes √ó 10 ranks + 10 ranks.
    - 5 suits of 3 times 10 ranks, or 5 suits of 30 ranks.
    - 3 suits of 5 times 10 ranks, or 3 suits of 50 ranks.
    - Extra suit of 10 ranks (rainbow).
  - **Sequential deck**: numbers from 0 to 159
    - 1 time: numbers from 0 to 159
    - 2 times: numbers from 0 to 59 (ignoring hundreds digit)
  - **Pyramidal deck**: 8 suits of 5 uneven ranks + 4 suits of 4 uneven ranks
    - 8 times: five 1s, four 2s, three 3s, two 4s, one 5.
    - 12 times: four 1s, three 2s, two 3s, one 4.
    - 10-level pyramidal deck. (Using the basic deck)
  - **Voting deck**: 60 √ó "yes" + 60 √ó "no" + 40 √ó "unknown"
  - **Custom deck**: by drawing.
- **Draw in the cards** to add words, points, icons, tiles, boards, extra ranks, etc.
  - Up to 16 drawing slots in each card, grouped in 5 drawing areas.
  - Use a pencil to erase any mistakes.
  - Designed to let you draw twice, upright and upside-down, to make cards work both ways.
  - Big enough for handwriting, but not too much.
  - Varied shapes strategically placed, to cover a wide variety of needs and keep organization.
- **Counting systems** using the cards' back face. For counting: points, coins, lives, etc.
  - Stacking method: Requires multiple cards, can comfortably count up to 30.
  - Pointing method: Requires 2 cards, can count from 0 to 10.
  - Chained pointind method: Requires `log10(MAX_VALUE) √ó 2` cards, can count up to very high numbers with very few cards.
- **Extra cards**: 2 additional cards.
  - 3 notes: To note down game boards, hints or rules.
  - 1 cover: With QR code pointing to the website.
- **Accessibility**:
  - Color-blind friendly: Distinct shapes and colors for the suits.
  - All suits are emojis, so you can easily write helper texts on your phone and send them to the players.
